<paragraph blockId="22.[1271,2255,386,1898]" pageId="22" pageNumber="85">
<typeStatus box="[1321,1410,1122,1161]" pageId="22" pageNumber="85">Type</typeStatus>
locality. Behind 'Kyndalyn' homestead, 
<quantity box="[2145,2252,1122,1161]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="22" pageNumber="85" unit="km" value="10.0">10 km</quantity>
south-west of Somerton, NSW (Locality 24).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[1271,2255,386,1898]" pageId="22" pageNumber="85">Stratigraphic position. In base of oolitic limestone in the Kyndalyn Mudstone Member of the Merlewood Formation.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[1271,2255,386,1898]" box="[1322,2129,1353,1391]" pageId="22" pageNumber="85">
Geographic distribution. 
<typeStatus box="[1794,1879,1353,1391]" pageId="22" pageNumber="85">Type</typeStatus>
locality only.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[1271,2255,386,1898]" box="[1322,2033,1399,1438]" pageId="22" pageNumber="85">Geological age. Middle or late Visean.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[1271,2255,386,1898]" pageId="22" pageNumber="85">
Etymology. Derived from the Latin 
<taxonomicName box="[1958,2093,1446,1484]" class="Gastropoda" family="Phymatopleuridae" genus="Borestus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleurotomariida" pageId="22" pageNumber="85" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="costatus">
<emphasis box="[1958,2093,1446,1484]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="85">costatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
meaning a rib; referring to collabral ribs on shell.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[1271,2255,386,1898]" pageId="22" pageNumber="85">
Remarks. This is an extremely rare species. Although a single specimen is available, the excellent preservation of the specimen warrants the naming of the specimen. 
<taxonomicName authority="Yoo, 1994" authorityName="Yoo" authorityYear="1994" box="[1271,1601,1675,1714]" class="Gastropoda" family="Palaeostylidae" genus="Leptozyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coenogastropoda incertae sedis" pageId="22" pageNumber="85" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="costata" status="n.sp.">
<emphasis box="[1271,1601,1675,1714]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="85">Leptozyga costata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1635,1712,1675,1714]" pageId="22" pageNumber="85" rank="species">n.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Yoo, 1994" authorityName="Yoo" authorityYear="1994" class="Gastropoda" family="Neotaenioglossa (awaiting allocation)" genus="Palaeozygopleura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neotaenioglossa" pageId="22" pageNumber="85" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="obesa" status="n.sp.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="85">Palaeozygopleura obesa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1395,1472,1721,1760]" pageId="22" pageNumber="85" rank="species">n.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Yoo" authorityName="Yoo" box="[1584,2037,1721,1760]" class="Gastropoda" family="Pseudozygopleuridae" genus="Hemizyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coenogastropoda incertae sedis" pageId="22" pageNumber="85" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="decussata">
<emphasis box="[1584,1940,1721,1760]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="85">Hemizyga decussata</emphasis>
Yoo
</taxonomicName>
in being a cyrtoconoid with collabral cords, but differs in being minute and in having deep sinuous ornament on the protoconch.
</paragraph>
